    public abstract class NodeStack<Self extends NodeStack>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    Advanced class for handling namespaces with virtually any separator character.

      • startsWith

        public boolean startsWith(@Nonnull
                          Self namespace,
                          boolean matchAtSeparator)
        Computes if this namespace starts with the provided namespace.

        ex: (Left being this namespace, right being the provided namespace) 

           True: "com.google.exampleSite.home" == "com.google.exampleSite"
   False: "com.google.exampleSite.home" == "com.google.example"
        Parameters:
        namespace - The namespace to compare this namespace to.
        matchAtSeparator - Should we only match each node or can the last node partially match? Setting this to FALSE would result in both examples above being TRUE.
        Returns:
        True if this namespace starts with the provided namespace, false otherwise.
